{Set Permissions in Linux}

Add write for group:
chmod g+w sample-original.txt

Remove read for group & others:
chmod go-r sample-original.txt

Full access for all:
chmod 777 sample-original.txt

User: rwx, Group: r, Others: none:
chmod 740 sample-original.txt

User: rw, Group: rx, Others: r:
chmod 654 sample-original.txt

User: rw, Group: r, Others: r:
chmod 644 sample-original.txt


{Configure IPv4 in Linux}

Show IP config (eth0):
ip addr show eth0 or ifconfig eth0

Remove IP from eth0:
ip a del 192.168.10.25/24 dev eth0
or
ip a flush dev eth0

Add IP to eth0:
ip a add 192.168.10.119/24 brd + dev eth0

Show routing table:
route -n

Set default gateway:
route add default gw 192.168.10.1 eth0

Check DNS servers:
cat /etc/resolv.conf

Set DNS servers:


{Linux System Commands}

Live process view:
top or htop

List all processes:
ps -A

Running Firefox in background then,

Find Firefox PID:
ps -A | grep firefox

Kill process by PID:
kill <PID of firefox>

Check for upgrades:
apt dist-upgrade -y

Remove unused packages:
apt autoremove -y

Upgrade packages:
apt upgrade -y
